Refined, Beginner-Friendly Project Report (as per professor's expectations)
1. Introduction

CNC (Computer Numerical Control) machines are widely used in manufacturing. In India, millions of MSMEs depend on CNC machines for daily production. However, most small workshops face several problems:

They cannot see machine performance in real time

Machine breakdowns happen unexpectedly

Maintenance logs are manual and inaccurate

Defects are found late

Machine, operator, and job data is not digitized

Because of this, production gets delayed, costs increase, and decision-making is mostly guesswork.

To solve these challenges, CNCMate is proposed as a data-driven AI analytics platform that uses IoT-based data collection, data engineering, and machine learning to:

monitor machines in real time

predict failures before they occur

track jobs, operators, and defects

provide dashboards and reports

This project focuses mainly on the data science and machine learning parts, keeping the technical development simple and achievable.

2. Project Objectives (Simplified)

The main goals of CNCMate are:

Predict machine failures in advance using ML models

Analyze CNC machine performance through dashboards

Track tool life and estimate when tools need replacement

Perform defect analytics using collected data

Digitize CNC operations such as job details and operator logs

Generate automated reports for supervisors and owners

These objectives help MSMEs reduce downtime and improve productivity through data-driven insights.

3. Problems in the Industry (Simplified Table)
Problem	Why It Is a Problem
No real-time visibility	Owners don‚Äôt know what's happening inside the machine
Manual logging	Leads to mistakes and missing information
Unplanned breakdowns	Production stops suddenly & increases repair cost
Poor defect tracking	Quality control becomes weak
No predictive maintenance	Failures occur without warning
No OEE measurement	Cannot evaluate productivity

These problems make small factories inefficient and uncompetitive.

4. Proposed Solution ‚Äì CNCMate (Simplified Overview)

CNCMate provides the following major features:

1. Live Monitoring (Basic IoT Simulation Used)

Machine status: ON/OFF/IDLE

Spindle speed

Temperature

Vibration

Tool usage

2. Predictive Maintenance (Main ML Component)

ML models predict:

spindle problems

overheating

vibration-based failures

3. Tool Life Estimation

Estimate remaining tool life based on historical data trends.

4. Defect Tracking (Manual + Simple Analytics)

Track number of defects per job, per shift, etc.

Identify patterns causing defects

5. Job and Operator Tracking

Digitally store job details and operator productivity.

6. Dashboards and Reports

Using Streamlit dashboards and auto-generated reports (PDF/Excel).

üí° This refined version avoids full-stack development complexity, keeping it aligned with Data Science workload.

5. System Architecture (Simple & Beginner-Friendly)
Step-by-step Flow:

Data Generation / Collection

Simulated CNC data (temp, vibration, speed, tool usage)

Stored in CSV or SQLite/PostgreSQL

Data Engineering

Cleaning

Filling missing values

Creating rolling averages

Labelling failures

EDA (Exploratory Data Analysis)

Trends of temperature, vibration

Identifying patterns before failure

Visualizations

Machine Learning Models

Failure prediction (classification)

Anomaly detection

Tool life estimation

Model Deployment (Basic)

FastAPI endpoint for prediction

Dashboard

Real-time metrics

Failure probability

Tool life

Operator & job analytics

